{% comment %}
  fancyfy runtime token bridge — ADR-003 §3.

  Declares any fancyfy-exclusive custom properties (category C of ADR-003 §2).
  This file is intentionally thin: fancyfy does NOT redeclare tokens that
  Horizon already provides. Horizon's theme-styles-variables emits all global
  design tokens on :root, and color-scheme tokens inside .color-scheme-N.

  Sections add their own --fcy-* declarations here only when justified
  per ADR-003 §2 Category C. Add a setting to `config/settings_schema.json`
  under the "Fancyfy — Extensions" group when the token is merchant-editable.
{% endcomment %}
<style id="fcy-tokens">
  :root {
    /* === fancyfy-exclusive tokens (ADR-003 §2 category C) ===
       Horizon has no equivalent for these. Naimies F1 — derived from Figma
       (fileKey zTPx8gXVv7dtebfV3448hL). */
    --fcy-color-accent: #fedc5c;
    --fcy-color-accent-contrast: #0a0a0a;
    --fcy-color-success: #008236;
    --fcy-color-success-surface: #0d8756;
    --fcy-color-success-surface-contrast: #ffffff;
  }
</style>
